00:33.453 --> 00:35.210
He said he just needs six months.

00:35.235 --> 00:36.593
Six months.

00:36.618 --> 00:38.454
MAUREEN: Do you know
your husband's a homosexual?

00:38.478 --> 00:40.610
He has that new disease that
all the gay men are spreading.

00:40.634 --> 00:41.634
That's a lie.

00:41.659 --> 00:44.289
He's the third man my
husband's seen who's had it.

00:44.314 --> 00:45.565
The first two are dead.

00:45.590 --> 00:46.906
You need care.

00:46.931 --> 00:49.983
Karl, you think I'd leave
you at a time like this?

00:50.008 --> 00:51.109
TOMMY: Cancel the trip?

00:51.134 --> 00:52.134
That's not fair.

00:52.159 --> 00:54.726
This was supposed to be
the best summer of my life.

00:54.751 --> 00:56.920
And this could be the last
summer of Karl's life,

00:56.945 --> 00:58.696
so please stop sulking.

00:59.714 --> 01:01.468
NAOMI: What's happened to my boy?

01:01.493 --> 01:03.218
Tommy's been in a car accident.

01:03.243 --> 01:04.812
He needed some stitches.

01:04.837 --> 01:06.207
What in the world?

01:06.232 --> 01:07.484
NURSE: Is that a tattoo?

01:07.509 --> 01:09.135
One of these days he'll regret that.

01:09.160 --> 01:10.578
So will she.

01:10.603 --> 01:12.421
- Oh. Wow.
- Right?

01:12.446 --> 01:14.960
- You bought me a car?
- I said I would take care of you.

01:15.599 --> 01:16.882
