02:54.633 --> 02:57.187
<i>EMILY: My name is Emily Stanton.</i>

02:58.570 --> 03:01.257
<i>I was killed over two years ago,</i>

03:01.282 --> 03:04.585
<i>but my mama still thinks
about me every day.</i>

03:05.145 --> 03:07.914
<i>Even when she's just
putting on lipstick,</i>

03:07.939 --> 03:11.281
<i>she'll suddenly remember
how much she loved me.</i>

03:13.031 --> 03:15.648
<i>I look down on Mama from heaven.</i>

03:15.673 --> 03:18.384
<i>I watch her because
I'm worried about her.</i>

03:19.320 --> 03:21.593
<i>She's not happy,</i>

03:21.618 --> 03:23.851
<i>but Daddy doesn't know...</i>

03:23.876 --> 03:26.101
<i>because she keeps smiling.</i>

03:26.729 --> 03:29.375
<i>Mama is very angry with him,</i>

03:29.400 --> 03:31.101
<i>and I have a feeling</i>

03:31.126 --> 03:33.726
<i>that she's gonna do something awful.</i>

03:34.515 --> 03:36.515
So, what have you got
planned for the day?

03:36.540 --> 03:37.917
Oh, nothing much.

03:37.942 --> 03:40.111
I'll be spending time with a new friend.

03:40.136 --> 03:42.476
Oh? What's her name?

03:43.276 --> 03:44.657
June.

03:45.108 --> 03:47.911
I have a feeling you'd really like her.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.578
And what are you two doing?

03:49.603 --> 03:52.498
I offered to drive her to
a doctor's appointment,

03:52.523 --> 03:54.025
but that's really just an excuse

03:54.050 --> 03:56.377
for me to talk to her
about the man she's seeing.

03:56.402 --> 03:57.828
Why?

03:57.853 --> 03:59.882
I don't approve of the relationship,

04:00.249 --> 04:02.414
so I've decided to break them up.

04:02.439 --> 04:04.941
Beth Ann, that's not nice.

04:04.966 --> 04:06.703
Maybe not,

04:07.098 --> 04:08.875
but it's necessary.

04:11.021 --> 04:13.440
<i>ED: My name is Edmund Harte.</i>

04:13.465 --> 04:16.132
<i>I was 57 when I died.</i>

04:17.017 --> 04:20.229
<i>That's how my bitch
wife became my widow.</i>

04:22.168 --> 04:25.421
<i>I check in from time to time
to see how my kid is doing,</i>

04:26.194 --> 04:28.328
<i>'cause I'm worried about him.</i>

04:29.390 --> 04:32.171
<i>His mother is desperate to control him,</i>

04:33.867 --> 04:35.525
<i>but Tommy's a man now,</i>

04:35.550 --> 04:37.539
<i>able to make his own choices.</i>

04:38.500 --> 04:40.964
<i>And I know Naomi is going to fight him</i>

04:40.989 --> 04:42.734
<i>every step of the way.</i>

04:44.560 --> 04:45.843
Good luck, kid.

04:47.223 --> 04:48.875
My poor baby.

04:50.554 --> 04:51.914
Simone?

04:54.028 --> 04:55.796
No, it's me.

04:58.982 --> 05:01.453
Mom. Oh, God.

05:01.478 --> 05:03.522
It's okay, I know everything.

05:03.867 --> 05:06.097
You don't have to protect her anymore.

05:06.382 --> 05:08.742
And I am not angry,

05:09.225 --> 05:10.937
not at you anyway.

05:12.554 --> 05:13.929
NURSE: Mrs. Harte?

05:14.230 --> 05:16.070
The hospital administrator has arrived.

05:16.095 --> 05:17.523
Ah, thank you.

05:21.555 --> 05:24.590
Mr. Kern, thank you so much
for agreeing to see me.

05:24.615 --> 05:25.950
How can I help you, Ms. Harte?

05:25.975 --> 05:28.429
Do you happen to know Simone Grove?

05:28.454 --> 05:31.242
I do. She's one of our
hospital's biggest fundraisers.

05:31.276 --> 05:34.737
Yes. Well, in between benefit galas,

05:34.762 --> 05:37.773
it seems that Simone has
been molesting my son,

05:38.358 --> 05:40.632
possibly for years.

05:40.744 --> 05:43.757
If you allow her to
visit or even phone him,

05:43.782 --> 05:46.750
I will sue this hospital and I will win.

05:46.971 --> 05:48.823
Do you understand?

05:49.195 --> 05:53.536
Yes. Um, I'm-I'm so sorry.

05:53.561 --> 05:55.437
Rest assured,
this matter will be handled

05:55.462 --> 05:57.165
with the utmost discretion.

05:57.190 --> 05:59.148
No need to be discreet on my account.

05:59.173 --> 06:01.008
I intend on telling
everyone in this town

06:01.033 --> 06:03.054
what that woman has done to my family.

06:05.732 --> 06:07.150
Nice tie.

06:14.187 --> 06:16.554
<i>VERNA: My name is Verna Roy.</i>

06:16.813 --> 06:19.671
<i>I was 32 when I died in a fire.</i>

06:20.898 --> 06:21.898
<i>At the time,</i>

06:21.923 --> 06:24.921
<i>I was a foster mother
to this one right here.</i>

06:26.149 --> 06:28.781
<i>I don't like to talk
bad about the living,</i>

06:28.806 --> 06:31.539
<i>but this gal's pure poison.</i>

06:33.039 --> 06:34.827
<i>I can see she's now living</i>

06:34.852 --> 06:37.781
<i>in a fancy house with pretty things.</i>

06:37.806 --> 06:41.250
<i>That means some man
has fallen for her act.</i>

06:41.275 --> 06:43.656
Eli, you're gonna be late!

06:43.681 --> 06:46.234
<i>VERNA: Stupid son of a bitch.</i>

06:47.195 --> 06:49.609
<i>He don't know what she's capable of,</i>

06:49.634 --> 06:52.887
<i>but I got a feeling
he's about to find out.</i>

06:52.912 --> 06:53.996
Wow.

06:54.021 --> 06:55.790
Moving kind of slow today.

06:55.815 --> 06:57.807
What did you give me last night,
a horse tranquilizer?

06:57.831 --> 06:59.267
Well, I wouldn't have
to give you anything

06:59.291 --> 07:01.477
if you'd stop doing coke after 10:00.

07:01.502 --> 07:02.962
You talk like I have self-control.

07:02.987 --> 07:04.239
I'm almost embarrassed for you.

07:04.264 --> 07:06.563
Well, whatever. Here, look.

07:06.588 --> 07:07.881
I've got a surprise.

07:08.302 --> 07:10.288
ELI: Whoa. What's the occasion?

07:10.313 --> 07:12.032
It's Scorsese day.

07:12.057 --> 07:14.390
Oh, look, it's just a meeting.

07:14.415 --> 07:15.861
I mean, the odds of
him directing my movie

07:15.885 --> 07:16.939
are, like, a million to one.

07:16.963 --> 07:19.431
He loved your script.
I think that's a big deal.

07:19.456 --> 07:21.875
God, I just...
I hope I can burn this off by 10:00.

07:21.900 --> 07:23.110
I feel so out of it.

07:23.390 --> 07:25.711
Well, luckily for you,

07:25.736 --> 07:28.649
I know how to prepare
a well-balanced meal.

07:29.431 --> 07:31.409
Mmm. You take such good care of me.

07:35.382 --> 07:38.141
Scorsese's gonna direct
your movie, I know it,

07:38.166 --> 07:41.210
and it's gonna be a big hit
and we are going to be so rich.

07:41.235 --> 07:42.696
From your lips...

07:43.001 --> 07:46.743
I always knew something exciting
would happen to me one day.

07:46.987 --> 07:48.609
I think this is it.

07:48.634 --> 07:51.016
Again, all right, it's just a meeting.

07:51.285 --> 07:52.852
I'm not worried.

07:53.377 --> 07:56.087
This is the year where
all my dreams come true.

07:57.775 --> 08:01.009
[CHUCKLES]

08:03.034 --> 08:04.625
Hello, Jenny.

08:05.727 --> 08:07.649
Oh, Mr. and Mrs. Grove.

08:07.674 --> 08:09.977
Please tell me you have
the veal piccata tonight.

08:10.002 --> 08:12.466
Just the thought of it
has kept me going all day.

08:12.491 --> 08:16.134
I'm sorry, but I can't seat you.

08:16.159 --> 08:18.639
Oh... oh, you're not overbooked again?

08:18.664 --> 08:20.712
Well, I see our usual table is empty.

08:20.737 --> 08:22.322
I don't know who you promised it to,

08:22.347 --> 08:24.975
but they should have gotten here sooner.

08:28.385 --> 08:30.032
KARL: Here we are, my darling.

08:31.319 --> 08:32.320
Thank you.

08:32.954 --> 08:34.416
- There we go.
- Anyway, I've been trying to talk

08:34.440 --> 08:37.423
to Tommy in the hospital,
but I can't seem to get through to him.

08:37.448 --> 08:38.700
It's bizarre.

08:39.298 --> 08:40.995
Sorry, darling, is it my imagination,

08:41.020 --> 08:42.345
or are people staring at us?

08:42.370 --> 08:43.462
I'm wearing Givenchy.

08:43.487 --> 08:45.698
They always stare when I wear Givenchy.

08:46.282 --> 08:50.345
No, no, I think, actually,
they're just staring at me.

08:52.471 --> 08:53.766
You're right.

08:54.033 --> 08:56.993
It must be your jacket.
I told you plaid is over.

08:58.795 --> 08:59.921
Mr. and Mrs. Grove.

08:59.946 --> 09:01.681
Henry, how lovely to see you.

09:01.706 --> 09:04.102
I'm terribly sorry, but I'm afraid
I have to ask you to leave.

09:04.126 --> 09:06.962
Oh, for God's sake,
he can take the jacket off.

09:07.610 --> 09:08.610
What's wrong?

09:08.635 --> 09:10.196
Someone should have notified you.

09:10.221 --> 09:12.765
Your membership to the
club has been revoked.

09:13.360 --> 09:15.126
[SCOFFS] You can't be serious.

09:15.151 --> 09:17.391
The committee met this afternoon.
The vote was unanimous.

09:18.149 --> 09:21.602
W... We've belonged to
this club for 15 years.

09:21.627 --> 09:23.704
Why on earth would you
want to kick us out?

09:23.729 --> 09:26.315
It's because I'm ill, isn't it?

09:26.340 --> 09:27.967
We have to protect our members.

09:27.992 --> 09:29.727
It's a sexually transmitted disease.

09:29.752 --> 09:32.095
You don't get it by sharing
a fucking tennis court.

09:32.120 --> 09:35.821
All the same, your membership
contract has a morals clause.

09:36.537 --> 09:39.227
[GASPS] Of all the people here,

09:39.252 --> 09:41.531
you think we're the
ones who lack morals?

09:41.556 --> 09:44.165
Mason Reed over there
is addicted to heroin,

09:44.190 --> 09:47.173
and Susan Paul is sleeping
with her brother-in-law.

09:47.198 --> 09:50.423
And you don't want to know
what happens in the club sauna.

09:51.220 --> 09:52.790
That's not helpful.

09:52.815 --> 09:56.529
For the last time,
Mr. and Mrs. Grove, please go.

09:57.708 --> 09:59.235
Shall we?

10:01.157 --> 10:03.024
Would you mind terribly...

10:03.436 --> 10:05.396
Oh, thank you.

10:05.829 --> 10:07.690
Goodbye, Henry.

10:07.715 --> 10:09.092
[PATRONS GASP AND MURMUR]

10:09.117 --> 10:11.087
Good for you, dear.

10:11.405 --> 10:15.056
Oh, don't worry, Henry,
I'm gonna drink mine.

10:26.797 --> 10:29.216
Thank you again for
recommending this obstetrician.

10:29.241 --> 10:31.337
I talked to him on the phone,
he sounds wonderful.

10:33.191 --> 10:34.191
Sheila?

10:34.216 --> 10:36.282
- Hmm?
- [CHUCKLES]

10:36.307 --> 10:37.767
What are you thinking about?

10:37.792 --> 10:40.735
Uh, your upcoming wedding.

10:40.760 --> 10:43.266
Aw. You excited for me?

10:43.291 --> 10:45.210
- [CHUCKLES]
- I am.

10:45.235 --> 10:46.620
Oh...

10:47.509 --> 10:48.766
I'm curious,

10:48.791 --> 10:51.836
have you had a chance to
discuss Rob's expectations?

10:52.266 --> 10:55.516
- Expectations?
- Well, you want a career.

10:55.780 --> 10:58.227
Some men don't allow
their wives to work.

10:58.252 --> 11:00.329
Oh, well,
Rob knows I want to be a singer.

11:00.354 --> 11:01.969
We've talked about it a lot.

11:02.188 --> 11:04.235
Since you've become pregnant?

11:04.512 --> 11:05.860
Well...

11:08.703 --> 11:09.703
No.

11:09.728 --> 11:11.618
Might be time for a chat.

11:12.229 --> 11:14.431
Rob strikes me as the
kind of man who'd prefer

11:14.456 --> 11:15.832
his wife to stay home.

11:15.857 --> 11:17.650
You talk like you know him.

11:18.681 --> 11:20.235
Oh, I know his type.

11:20.260 --> 11:22.782
Rich, successful.

11:22.807 --> 11:25.720
That kind of man wants
his wife in the kitchen,

11:25.744 --> 11:28.548
feeding the kids and
pouring his martini.

11:28.573 --> 11:30.165
Rob's not like that.

11:30.752 --> 11:33.509
You absolutely sure?

11:36.834 --> 11:38.759
Well, he better be okay with it,

11:39.556 --> 11:41.342
or we're gonna have a problem.

11:42.016 --> 11:44.696
That's what I was thinking.

11:55.440 --> 11:58.696
Okay, according to this,
we're looking for Suite 203.

12:22.529 --> 12:23.688
APRIL: Sheila.

12:23.838 --> 12:25.095
Coming!

12:32.117 --> 12:33.423
You okay?

12:34.052 --> 12:36.689
Yeah, man, I'm sorry,
I'm just, I'm really nervous.

12:36.714 --> 12:39.091
You know, I basically
grew up on Scorsese movies.

12:40.410 --> 12:42.063
Hey, buddy, do me a favor.

12:42.088 --> 12:44.165
I want you to manage your expectations

12:44.190 --> 12:45.406
before we walk in here.

12:45.681 --> 12:48.350
Shit. Why? Is he an asshole?

12:48.375 --> 12:50.627
Let's just say it isn't
gonna be the meeting

12:50.652 --> 12:52.024
you were hoping for.

12:55.500 --> 12:56.696
What the fuck?

12:56.721 --> 12:58.095
Hello, Eli.

12:58.373 --> 12:59.727
[SCOFFS]

12:59.752 --> 13:01.337
So I was never meeting Scorsese?

13:01.362 --> 13:03.954
Sorry. You really need to hear her out.

13:03.979 --> 13:05.204
Why?

13:05.953 --> 13:08.137
Is this some sort of
bullshit intervention?

13:08.162 --> 13:09.618
Something like that.

13:10.165 --> 13:12.220
I'm gonna go get some coffee.

13:12.245 --> 13:13.602
You want a cup?

13:15.122 --> 13:18.579
No. Cool. Cool.

13:22.766 --> 13:24.048
Well, this is humiliating.

13:24.073 --> 13:26.306
Eli, that wasn't my intention.

13:26.769 --> 13:29.531
But we need to talk. Privately.

13:29.556 --> 13:30.759
About?

13:31.664 --> 13:33.384
Irene Tabatchnick.

13:34.826 --> 13:36.620
Who the hell's Irene Tabatchnick?

13:37.962 --> 13:40.051
The woman who's been
sleeping in our bed.

13:43.688 --> 13:45.887
You may want to sit down
for the rest of this.

13:49.479 --> 13:51.395
If Dr. Bennett's wife told people,

13:51.420 --> 13:54.433
that is a violation of
doctor-patient confidentiality.

13:55.067 --> 13:56.961
We should have his license revoked.

13:57.160 --> 14:00.422
How much energy do we really
want to devote to all this?

14:00.447 --> 14:03.033
This is discrimination.
We have to fight back.

14:03.058 --> 14:07.196
And draw more attention to
my sex life and my disease?

14:07.629 --> 14:09.317
You don't think people
will be sympathetic?

14:09.342 --> 14:10.969
On the contrary.

14:10.994 --> 14:12.996
I think the situation's
going to get much worse

14:13.021 --> 14:14.574
before it gets better.

14:15.237 --> 14:16.363
Well, we won't dwell on it.

14:16.388 --> 14:17.864
Why don't you take a
nice, long, hot bath?

14:17.888 --> 14:19.098
You seem exhausted.

14:19.123 --> 14:20.199
Mm.

14:20.661 --> 14:22.934
Turns out being shunned by Republicans

14:22.959 --> 14:25.082
takes rather a lot out of a person.

14:28.396 --> 14:30.199
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

14:33.831 --> 14:35.749
Naomi, I've been trying to reach you.

14:35.774 --> 14:36.900
How's Tommy?

14:36.925 --> 14:38.387
He's fine.

14:39.232 --> 14:40.676
Well, I keep calling the hospital,

14:40.701 --> 14:42.465
but I can never seem to get through.

14:43.455 --> 14:44.606
What are in the bags?

14:44.631 --> 14:46.235
Ah, presents.

14:46.488 --> 14:47.568
For me?

14:47.593 --> 14:48.809
