14:48.834 --> 14:51.824
Every gift you ever gave me,
I'm returning them.

14:52.231 --> 14:53.426
I don't understand.

14:53.451 --> 14:55.707
This lovely figurine you got me

14:55.732 --> 14:57.129
while you were in Bavaria.

14:57.154 --> 14:58.989
I don't want it anymore.

15:01.731 --> 15:02.918
What the hell?!

15:02.943 --> 15:06.387
Or this sweet silver music box.

15:06.412 --> 15:08.090
I don't need that either.

15:09.723 --> 15:11.100
Have you lost your mind?

15:11.125 --> 15:12.247
I have,

15:12.591 --> 15:16.098
because I know what you did to my son.

15:16.981 --> 15:18.114
Oh.

15:18.139 --> 15:19.294
That's all you have to say?

15:19.829 --> 15:21.059
I-I understand your anger,

15:21.084 --> 15:22.717
but if you'll just give
me a chance to explain...

15:22.741 --> 15:24.497
I will, just as soon as I return

15:24.522 --> 15:26.774
this darling crystal paperweight.

15:28.550 --> 15:29.550
Stop it!

15:29.575 --> 15:31.567
You can't come in here
and destroy my home.

15:31.592 --> 15:32.934
Why not?

15:33.484 --> 15:35.444
You destroyed my life.

15:35.469 --> 15:37.091
If we can't talk about this rationally,

15:37.116 --> 15:38.326
I will call the police.

15:38.351 --> 15:40.192
Go ahead, I'm leaving.

15:40.217 --> 15:42.594
You know, I would say that I'll
see you at the country club,

15:42.619 --> 15:44.376
but, you know...

15:45.044 --> 15:46.559
It was you.

15:46.584 --> 15:48.169
Who got you voted out?

15:48.194 --> 15:49.489
Yes.

15:49.514 --> 15:52.442
The board didn't need much persuading
once they knew that Karl

15:52.467 --> 15:54.928
was spreading a deadly disease.

15:54.953 --> 15:56.895
We were unceremoniously ejected

15:56.920 --> 15:58.575
in front of all of our friends.

15:58.925 --> 16:00.636
I hope you're satisfied.

16:00.844 --> 16:02.606
Satisfied?

16:04.758 --> 16:08.178
You seduced my child.

16:08.203 --> 16:10.653
Do you honestly think
that I would be satisfied

16:10.678 --> 16:12.583
just getting you kicked
out of a country club?

16:12.853 --> 16:16.440
I am just getting started, bitch.

16:16.465 --> 16:19.628
And before I am done, I will burn you,

16:19.653 --> 16:23.619
your business, and this poorly
decorated shithole

16:23.644 --> 16:25.145
to the ground!

16:26.511 --> 16:28.447
Satisfied?

16:28.969 --> 16:30.260
[SCOFFS]

16:36.829 --> 16:38.163
[DOOR SLAMS]

16:40.932 --> 16:42.588
What the hell happened here?

16:43.632 --> 16:45.627
Things just got worse.

16:58.727 --> 17:01.010
[DOORBELL RINGS]

17:03.311 --> 17:04.727
Sorry to intrude.

17:04.752 --> 17:07.088
I was wondering if I could
borrow a cup of sugar.

17:07.113 --> 17:10.010
I'm baking a cake,
and I forgot to check my pantry.

17:11.418 --> 17:13.586
You don't really need
a cup of sugar, do you?

17:15.360 --> 17:16.509
No.

17:16.889 --> 17:18.474
Come on in.

17:28.393 --> 17:30.283
Can I ask what happened?

17:31.111 --> 17:33.471
We were at a department store,

17:34.389 --> 17:37.205
and the sales clerk recognized me.

17:37.230 --> 17:39.065
It turns out that he'd
gone to my high school

17:39.090 --> 17:40.565
two years after I did,

17:41.057 --> 17:43.143
so he knew a lot of my old friends.

17:43.168 --> 17:44.994
We only spoke for five minutes.

17:46.562 --> 17:47.979
After we got back,

17:48.481 --> 17:51.739
Ralph accused me
of trying to seduce the man.

17:51.764 --> 17:53.146
That's why?

17:56.498 --> 17:58.041
He thought you were flirting?

17:58.066 --> 18:00.489
He gets jealous. He can't help it.

18:00.514 --> 18:03.818
I don't understand how
you can live like this.

18:04.312 --> 18:06.669
You can't possibly be happy.

18:06.694 --> 18:07.732
I'm not.

18:07.757 --> 18:09.759
So why don't you leave?

18:11.265 --> 18:13.060
I could ask you the same question.

18:13.732 --> 18:15.302
What?

18:15.447 --> 18:17.239
Isn't your husband cheating on you?

18:19.685 --> 18:20.811
He is.

18:21.190 --> 18:22.864
I had a feeling you knew.

18:24.379 --> 18:25.497
So why don't you leave him?

18:25.522 --> 18:28.013
It's an entirely different situation.

18:28.038 --> 18:29.664
He's humiliating you.

18:30.022 --> 18:31.710
That's got to hurt.

18:31.735 --> 18:33.310
It does.

18:33.335 --> 18:35.239
Will you ever trust him again?

18:38.774 --> 18:40.067
No.

18:40.181 --> 18:41.802
And if you did leave Rob,

18:42.511 --> 18:44.097
would he try and kill you?

18:44.122 --> 18:45.489
Of course not.

18:45.514 --> 18:47.771
Well, my husband would.

18:48.216 --> 18:49.333
He likes to threaten me

18:49.358 --> 18:52.122
with a loaded gun he keeps
in his bedside drawer.

18:52.524 --> 18:54.185
So I stay.

18:55.802 --> 18:57.997
What in God's name is your excuse?

19:00.224 --> 19:02.568
I keep hoping for a miracle.

19:05.290 --> 19:07.739
That one day everything will change.

19:09.114 --> 19:11.091
You and I should be friends.

19:12.085 --> 19:13.778
We have a lot in common.

19:18.575 --> 19:20.771
Irene Tabatchnick is from Ohio.

19:21.173 --> 19:23.259
By the time she was
16, she was thrown out

19:23.284 --> 19:24.739
of three foster homes.

19:24.764 --> 19:27.341
The first two times,
Irene had been caught stealing cash.

19:27.366 --> 19:29.177
So what? She was young. She was a kid.

19:29.202 --> 19:30.700
She was kicked out of her third home

19:30.725 --> 19:32.268
because her foster mother accused her

19:32.293 --> 19:34.255
of trying to seduce her husband.

19:34.280 --> 19:35.716
Maybe the woman was in denial

19:35.741 --> 19:36.927
about what her husband was up to.

19:36.951 --> 19:38.536
Oh, we'll never know.

19:38.561 --> 19:40.419
A week later, that house burned down.

19:40.989 --> 19:42.574
Burned down?

19:44.318 --> 19:46.232
Those foster parents died, Eli.

19:46.997 --> 19:49.489
And Irene Tabatchnick just disappeared.

19:49.974 --> 19:50.975
So, what, you think she...?

19:50.999 --> 19:53.310
I mean, we can't prove anything,

19:53.661 --> 19:56.293
but the cops in Ohio
are dying to talk to her.

19:57.978 --> 20:00.106
Th-This is just so stupid.

20:00.131 --> 20:02.301
This is... There's no way that Jade...

20:02.326 --> 20:03.551
Her name is Irene.

20:03.576 --> 20:04.918
Whatever.

20:06.371 --> 20:07.371
She loves us.

20:07.396 --> 20:10.106
If she loved you,
would she keep giving you cocaine?

20:10.131 --> 20:12.074
You look terrible, by the way.

20:12.099 --> 20:13.302
Thank you.

20:15.406 --> 20:16.848
Come on, Eli.

20:16.873 --> 20:19.751
She keeps you high so she
can take advantage of you.

20:20.049 --> 20:21.996
So that you let her live in our house,

20:22.021 --> 20:23.723
so that you buy her a new car.

20:23.748 --> 20:25.366
You know, you didn't need to trick me

20:25.391 --> 20:27.183
to have this conversation, Taylor.

20:27.208 --> 20:28.585
You could've just called.

20:28.610 --> 20:30.718
I did call. Every hour.

20:30.743 --> 20:32.508
What are you talking about?
You never called me.

20:32.532 --> 20:34.218
I most certainly did.

20:35.051 --> 20:37.470
Look. Look.

20:38.015 --> 20:41.218
No missed calls. No voice mails.

20:42.319 --> 20:45.077
That sneaky bitch blocked my number.

20:46.913 --> 20:48.108
On my phone?

20:48.133 --> 20:50.179
She couldn't do that
without my pass code.

20:51.557 --> 20:53.390
Well, she has your pass code.

20:54.691 --> 20:56.132
How does she have that?

20:56.891 --> 20:58.429
I gave it to her.

20:59.943 --> 21:01.223
So you could take away my money.

21:01.248 --> 21:03.593
- To keep you from buying drugs.
- Jesus.

21:03.618 --> 21:05.187
You know what,
maybe she does take advantage of me,

21:05.211 --> 21:06.671
but at least she builds me up.

21:06.790 --> 21:08.561
She doesn't make me feel
like a fuck-up who's just

21:08.585 --> 21:10.044
destined to crash and burn.

21:10.069 --> 21:12.296
The only reason why I think
you're gonna crash and burn,

21:12.321 --> 21:14.483
Eli, is because you've done it before.

21:14.969 --> 21:16.887
You have no idea what it feels like

21:16.912 --> 21:18.580
to come home from work

21:18.605 --> 21:21.804
and then find you convulsing
on the kitchen floor.

21:22.342 --> 21:25.553
And then to call the ambulance,
which took forever.

21:29.248 --> 21:30.827
I'm not gonna do that again, Eli.

21:30.852 --> 21:32.077
I'm... [SIGHS]

21:32.102 --> 21:33.728
No one is asking you to.

21:34.957 --> 21:36.561
I don't need your help.

21:37.092 --> 21:40.163
I've got my career back. I'm fine.

21:41.111 --> 21:43.499
The only one here with a problem is you.

21:49.493 --> 21:50.869
You're an addict, Eli.

21:50.894 --> 21:52.469
You need to go to
rehab, and you know it.

21:52.493 --> 21:53.727
The only thing I know, Taylor, is that

21:53.751 --> 21:55.295
this conversation is over.

21:55.320 --> 21:56.460
- Eli, please stop...
- Stop!

21:56.485 --> 21:58.976
Enough! Let me go.

22:56.046 --> 22:57.327
[BETH ANN CHUCKLES]

22:57.352 --> 22:59.646
- You like your new ball, don't you?
- Yes.

22:59.672 --> 23:02.101
After dinner, we're going
to write a thank you note

23:02.126 --> 23:03.211
to Aunt Lydia.

23:03.236 --> 23:04.812
I don't know how to write.

23:04.837 --> 23:06.571
I'll do the writing.
You can draw a big heart

23:06.595 --> 23:08.236
right next to our names.

23:08.261 --> 23:10.828
Look, dear, your father forgot
to bring in the trash can.

23:10.853 --> 23:12.656
Play here for a second.
I'll be right back.

23:26.943 --> 23:28.016
Come along, Emily.

23:28.041 --> 23:29.854
Don't you want to show
your daddy your new ball?

23:29.878 --> 23:31.133
Yes.

23:34.621 --> 23:36.055
Hey there.

23:37.015 --> 23:38.523
What are you two doing home?

23:38.548 --> 23:40.351
I didn't expect you
back for another hour.

23:40.376 --> 23:41.969
Aunt Lydia wasn't feeling well.

23:41.994 --> 23:43.547
We had to cut our visit short.

23:43.572 --> 23:45.586
Hey, princess, what do you got there?

23:45.611 --> 23:48.961
A ball. Aunt Lydia gave it
to me for my birthday.

23:48.986 --> 23:50.586
Well...

23:51.672 --> 23:53.180
Her birthday was two months ago.

23:53.207 --> 23:55.039
Be nice. It's the thought that counts.

23:55.064 --> 23:56.719
Can I go play?

23:56.744 --> 23:58.398
Of course you can.

24:02.630 --> 24:03.704
Rob, did you lose a button?

24:03.728 --> 24:05.023
I just found one on the floor.

24:05.048 --> 24:07.133
Ah. Oh, I guess I did. Thanks.

24:07.158 --> 24:09.781
- Mama.
- I'm sorry, honey.

24:10.850 --> 24:12.055
Here you go.

24:12.080 --> 24:13.321
I'm making mac and cheese for dinner,

24:13.345 --> 24:14.930
so don't be too long, okay?

24:28.073 --> 24:29.805
[TIRES SKID]

24:29.830 --> 24:31.156
[LOUD THUMP]

24:32.794 --> 24:35.578
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

24:36.078 --> 24:38.080
[INDISTINCT ALARMED CHATTER]

24:58.175 --> 24:59.258
Honey?

24:59.283 --> 25:00.937
Someone call a doctor.

25:02.424 --> 25:04.391
[SCREAMING]

25:05.201 --> 25:06.201
Emily?

25:07.309 --> 25:09.400
Emily, honey, wake up.
Open your eyes.

25:09.424 --> 25:11.156
Open your eyes, honey.

25:11.181 --> 25:12.750
[SOBBING]: Open your eyes.

25:12.775 --> 25:13.805
Please wake up.

25:13.830 --> 25:16.234
Please... Please...

25:17.002 --> 25:18.469
What the hell?

25:25.930 --> 25:30.351
[SCREAMING]

25:31.970 --> 25:34.117
Who was driving this car?!

25:34.142 --> 25:36.391
Sh-She, uh, she-she came out

25:36.416 --> 25:38.680
of nowhere, mister, I swear.
I tried to stop...

25:58.711 --> 26:01.172
You left the gate open?

26:01.197 --> 26:04.200
- No. I'm sure I locked it.
- You're sure?

26:04.225 --> 26:06.023
Then how did Emily get
out of the backyard?

26:06.048 --> 26:08.539
The latch is six feet off the ground!

26:09.031 --> 26:12.398
I don't know. Maybe I forgot.

26:12.992 --> 26:14.930
You didn't lock the gate.

26:15.458 --> 26:17.258
You didn't lock the gate,

26:17.283 --> 26:19.410
and you let her out to play.

26:21.867 --> 26:23.633
[CRYING]: I had to make dinner.

26:23.658 --> 26:25.336
That's no excuse.

26:26.234 --> 26:29.445
Our baby is dead.

26:31.801 --> 26:32.945
I'm sorry.

26:32.970 --> 26:35.406
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

26:41.787 --> 26:44.391
I thought it was locked.

26:52.110 --> 26:54.154
[KISSES]

26:58.971 --> 27:00.639
Amy.

27:00.664 --> 27:02.781
I just got a call from Naomi.

27:02.806 --> 27:04.344
Does Karl have AIDS?

27:07.498 --> 27:08.969
How could you not tell me?

27:08.994 --> 27:10.867
Well, we thought we had time.

27:10.892 --> 27:13.311
I mean, as you can see,
I'm not exactly at death's door.

27:13.336 --> 27:15.380
He has all the best
doctors, so don't worry.

27:15.405 --> 27:17.781
Karl will absolutely be able
to walk you down the aisle.

27:17.806 --> 27:21.351
At this point, I'm not even
sure there will be a wedding.

27:21.734 --> 27:22.797
What?

27:22.822 --> 27:24.407
Naomi's called all of our friends

27:24.432 --> 27:25.961
and told them Karl is sick.

27:25.986 --> 27:27.779
People have been
canceling right and left.

27:27.804 --> 27:28.875
Oh, Lord.

27:28.900 --> 27:31.133
And if nobody's coming, why bother?

27:31.158 --> 27:34.695
Oh, I'm so sorry, my darling.
Is there anything we can do?

27:35.508 --> 27:36.719
Well...

27:37.275 --> 27:40.383
we might be able
to salvage this thing if...

27:40.508 --> 27:42.594
you didn't come.

27:42.619 --> 27:43.976
To the wedding?

27:45.564 --> 27:47.062
I understand.

27:47.087 --> 27:51.031
Uh, of course, I will stay home.

27:51.187 --> 27:52.480
Thank you.

27:52.727 --> 27:55.039
No. Karl has to be at the wedding.

27:55.064 --> 27:56.459
Who's gonna walk you down the aisle?

27:56.483 --> 27:57.817
You can do it.

27:57.842 --> 28:00.836
I did not spend $6,000
on an Armani dress

28:00.861 --> 28:02.079
just to give it a shared entrance.

28:02.103 --> 28:03.726
Okay, let's not argue.

28:04.149 --> 28:05.283
Thank you.

28:06.625 --> 28:07.883
I don't mind.

28:07.908 --> 28:09.326
No!

28:10.328 --> 28:11.641
We are a family.

28:11.666 --> 28:14.078
When bad things happen,
we're supposed to support each other.

28:14.103 --> 28:15.148
The way I see it,

28:15.173 --> 28:18.093
he is supporting me, by staying away.

28:18.651 --> 28:21.321
I have to call my guests and
tell them it's safe to come.

28:25.542 --> 28:27.437
Amy, think of what you're doing.

28:27.731 --> 28:29.328
You're choosing a few cowardly bigots

28:29.353 --> 28:30.859
over the man who raised you.

28:30.884 --> 28:32.047
I'm the bride.

28:32.072 --> 28:34.391
It's my day,
and I want it to be perfect.

28:34.699 --> 28:36.805
I am sorry if Karl's deadly illness

28:36.830 --> 28:39.290
is scraping some of the
glitter off of your event,

28:39.315 --> 28:42.047
but let's face it,
this won't be your last wedding.

28:42.570 --> 28:44.164
- Nice.
- More importantly,

28:44.189 --> 28:46.109
if Karl can't attend, I won't either.

28:46.134 --> 28:48.601
- Oh, Simone.
- Fine.

28:48.626 --> 28:51.726
Stay home.
You'll save me some embarrassment.

28:51.751 --> 28:54.508
Karl's not the only one
everybody's talking about.

28:58.426 --> 28:59.719
[DOOR CLOSES]

29:00.030 --> 29:01.773
My daughter is a monster.

29:01.798 --> 29:05.055
Well, she's a bride.
It's basically the same thing.

29:15.294 --> 29:16.758
[CAR HORN HONKS]

29:18.692 --> 29:19.984
Hey!

29:23.761 --> 29:26.258
So... how'd the meeting go?

29:26.283 --> 29:28.070
I want to hear everything.

29:31.324 --> 29:32.370
Well, let's just say

29:32.395 --> 29:34.522
that Scorsese's not gonna
be directing my movie.

29:35.453 --> 29:36.524
Oh, no.

29:36.549 --> 29:38.258
I'm so sorry.

29:40.069 --> 29:42.680
But at least he loved the script, right?

29:44.131 --> 29:46.092
- He did. Yeah.
- Good.

29:46.117 --> 29:48.970
Yeah. Yeah, he especially liked the part

29:48.995 --> 29:51.576
where Eva burns the drug
dealer's house down.

29:51.601 --> 29:53.541
[CHUCKLES] He liked that?

29:54.023 --> 29:55.289
Yeah.

29:56.461 --> 29:58.606
Yeah, he liked it so much,
he asked me how I came up with it,

29:58.630 --> 30:01.608
and, you know, of course I had
to tell him it was your idea.

30:01.633 --> 30:03.391
[LAUGHS]

30:03.416 --> 30:05.945
You didn't have to give me credit.

30:05.970 --> 30:07.422
Yeah, well...

30:09.000 --> 30:11.094
How did you come up with
that, by the way?

30:11.828 --> 30:13.453
Uh, it just came to me.

30:13.478 --> 30:15.045
Just out of the blue?

30:15.679 --> 30:17.156
Yeah.

30:20.876 --> 30:23.671
'Cause it-it's such
an unusual concept, you know,

30:23.696 --> 30:26.203
arson as a form of revenge.

30:28.234 --> 30:29.969
You have no idea how that came to you?

30:29.994 --> 30:31.648
Why does it matter?

30:32.609 --> 30:34.749
I-I'm-I'm just curious.

30:35.008 --> 30:37.126
I don't know...
It just popped into my head.

30:37.781 --> 30:39.521
Just, boop?

30:39.546 --> 30:40.964
[CLICKS TONGUE]

30:41.375 --> 30:43.091
Boop. Yeah.

30:45.677 --> 30:47.711
Sometimes, that happens.

30:49.239 --> 30:51.199
Is that how you came
up with the name Jade?

30:51.224 --> 30:52.617
It just popped into your head?

30:53.577 --> 30:54.686
What? [CHUCKLES]

30:54.711 --> 30:57.094
It suits you better than Irene,
I'll give you that.

30:59.540 --> 31:01.422
Who have you been talking to?

31:01.906 --> 31:03.611
Hey, watch the road.

31:03.636 --> 31:05.262
Eli, do not fuck with me.

31:05.287 --> 31:07.170
Or else what,
you're gonna burn down my house?

31:07.195 --> 31:08.828
You talked to Duke?

31:10.758 --> 31:13.513
Oh, my God. You did those things.

31:13.538 --> 31:15.665
Did what? What did he say about me?

31:15.690 --> 31:18.059
Oh, my God, you killed those people.
Oh, my God.

31:18.084 --> 31:20.562
- Eli, Eli, the man is a liar!
- Hey, hey.

31:20.587 --> 31:22.470
- All right, slow down, slow down.
- Eli, you can't believe

31:22.494 --> 31:24.664
- a fucking word he says!
- Jesus, watch out!

31:25.442 --> 31:26.750
[CRASH]

31:32.327 --> 31:34.621
Karl, it's after 11:00.

31:34.646 --> 31:36.440
When are you going to the gallery?

31:36.465 --> 31:38.092
When people stop assuming

31:38.117 --> 31:40.773
you can catch AIDS from a lithograph.

31:40.798 --> 31:42.984
Oh, screw them all.

31:43.610 --> 31:45.653
Shall we have lunch at the Huntington?

31:45.678 --> 31:47.734
- Well, if you're paying.
- Good.

31:47.759 --> 31:50.289
I can't spend another afternoon
staring at these walls.

31:50.314 --> 31:51.899
Oh, I can't either.

31:52.267 --> 31:55.234
What were we thinking
with all the damn purple?

31:57.547 --> 32:00.781
[INDISTINCT CHATTER NEARBY]

32:00.806 --> 32:03.000
- Is it just my imagination or...?
- No.

32:03.025 --> 32:05.187
No. They're staring at us.

32:05.212 --> 32:07.242
[SIGHS] What have we done now?

32:09.043 --> 32:10.851
[GASPS]

32:11.032 --> 32:13.172
_

32:13.400 --> 32:14.906
Oh, my God.

32:15.533 --> 32:16.953
Wha...

32:16.978 --> 32:19.022
Did anyone see who did this?

32:19.460 --> 32:21.945
Someone had to have seen something.

32:22.173 --> 32:24.820
Don't just gawk. Answer me!

32:24.845 --> 32:27.390
- Simone.
- [GASPS] Karl!

32:29.797 --> 32:32.476
I'm-I'm a little dizzy.
I just need to go inside and lie down.

32:32.501 --> 32:35.553
You need to see a doctor.
Can you make it to the car?

32:35.578 --> 32:37.538
Can someone please help us?

32:38.899 --> 32:40.781
Please help us to the car!

32:41.641 --> 32:43.211
Is he the one with AIDS?

32:43.236 --> 32:45.641
Who cares? He's a human being!

32:48.239 --> 32:49.609
Oh, thank you.

32:49.634 --> 32:51.164
Thank you so much.

32:53.469 --> 32:55.703
You know, I'm so grateful. [STAMMERS]

32:55.728 --> 32:57.937
I want to hire you to
work on our property.

32:57.962 --> 33:00.089
Darling,
he's worked for us for six years.

33:00.114 --> 33:03.159
Oh, of course.
Um, thank you very much, uh...

33:03.497 --> 33:05.958
- Julio.
- Right.

33:05.983 --> 33:07.992
Julio. Here you go.

33:12.213 --> 33:15.093
[BOTH PANTING]

33:15.118 --> 33:17.687
- Shit. Shit. Shit. Shit.
- [GROANS]

33:29.716 --> 33:34.716
[SIRENS WAILING]

33:40.401 --> 33:41.945
I have to go.

33:42.562 --> 33:44.105
What?

33:53.148 --> 33:55.967
- Mmm. [CHUCKLES]
- God, I missed you.

33:56.226 --> 33:57.952
I missed this.

33:57.977 --> 33:59.766
Mmm, me, too.

34:00.802 --> 34:02.562
[CHUCKLES]

34:05.517 --> 34:07.828
So, I had an interesting day.

34:07.853 --> 34:08.979
Yeah?

34:09.004 --> 34:11.756
I talked to Mr. Porter,
that fella who runs the nightclub,

34:11.781 --> 34:13.491
I told him about the baby.

34:13.516 --> 34:14.789
Ah.

34:16.192 --> 34:17.891
What did he have to say?

34:17.916 --> 34:21.156
Well, he said congratulations.

34:21.367 --> 34:23.953
He also said, once I have the baby,

34:23.978 --> 34:26.147
he wants me right back up on that stage.

34:28.071 --> 34:29.344
Isn't that terrific?

34:30.055 --> 34:31.219
Yeah.

34:31.244 --> 34:32.912
- Wow.
- [CHUCKLES]

34:40.828 --> 34:42.555
I knew you would think so.

34:42.580 --> 34:45.834
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

34:46.680 --> 34:49.992
But isn't it a little
early to talk about this?

34:50.017 --> 34:52.478
Why don't we see how you
feel after the baby arrives?

34:52.503 --> 34:53.945
I won't feel any different.

34:53.970 --> 34:57.008
Well, taking care of
a baby is hard work.

34:57.261 --> 34:59.722
You might be too tired to keep singing.

34:59.747 --> 35:01.999
I'll never be too tired to sing.

35:03.461 --> 35:05.211
We'll see.

35:07.367 --> 35:09.648
- Rob...
- Hmm?

35:09.847 --> 35:11.349
Hey.

35:11.815 --> 35:13.359
It's my dream.

35:15.112 --> 35:18.074
And dreams are great,

35:18.586 --> 35:20.797
but you have to be realistic.

35:20.822 --> 35:22.851
It's a tough business to break into.

35:22.876 --> 35:24.294
I know.

35:24.327 --> 35:27.900
My Beth Ann wanted to
be in show business, and...

35:28.484 --> 35:30.748
she finally came to her senses and...

35:31.756 --> 35:33.248
... gave it up. Thank God.

35:33.273 --> 35:35.240
Well, maybe I'm more
talented than she is.

35:35.265 --> 35:38.623
She wasn't half-bad.
She wanted to play piano.

35:38.816 --> 35:39.901
Piano?

35:39.926 --> 35:42.803
Yeah, she wanted to
be a concert pianist,

35:42.828 --> 35:44.912
which is ridiculous.

35:46.686 --> 35:48.264
But you do what you want.

35:49.662 --> 35:52.692
As long as dinner's on
the table when I get home,

35:52.947 --> 35:54.592
what do I care?

35:57.331 --> 35:59.423
You know, it's kind of funny.

35:59.448 --> 36:03.295
Uh, my friend Sheila also
wanted to be a concert pianist.

36:03.320 --> 36:05.740
Yeah? Small world.

36:06.512 --> 36:08.311
Well, I got to go.

36:08.986 --> 36:10.905
- I'll call you tonight.
- Mmm.

36:23.905 --> 36:25.239
DR. CHARLES: Mrs. Grove?

36:25.264 --> 36:26.351
Yes?

36:26.775 --> 36:28.360
Based on the initial exam,

36:28.385 --> 36:31.531
we think your husband probably
has Pneumocystis pneumonia,

36:31.556 --> 36:35.062
an infection common in men
with suppressed immune systems.

36:35.408 --> 36:36.914
How serious is it?

36:36.939 --> 36:39.359
Most patients recover with treatment.

36:39.384 --> 36:41.484
"Most"? Do you mean some don't?

36:41.509 --> 36:43.109
We're gonna run some tests,

36:43.703 --> 36:44.906
then we'll know more.

36:44.931 --> 36:46.187
Thank you.

36:58.272 --> 36:59.468
Naomi.

36:59.952 --> 37:01.234
Nurse, put that down

37:01.259 --> 37:03.054
- and call security.
- SIMONE: Don't bother.

37:03.079 --> 37:04.649
I just have one thing
to say and then I'll go.

37:04.673 --> 37:08.086
If you think I'm gonna let you
go anywhere near my child...

37:08.111 --> 37:10.547
I'm not here for Tommy.
I'm here to apologize.

37:10.572 --> 37:13.164
An apology? Now?

37:13.189 --> 37:15.148
Color me disinterested.

37:15.173 --> 37:17.156
Then just tell me what I have to do...

37:17.235 --> 37:19.156
to do to get you to leave Karl alone.

37:19.181 --> 37:20.975
I haven't done anything to him.

37:21.000 --> 37:23.914
You have spread your poison
and made him a pariah.

37:23.939 --> 37:25.066
He has lost friends,

37:25.091 --> 37:26.968
been banned from his daughter's wedding,

37:26.993 --> 37:28.995
had his home vandalized.

37:29.020 --> 37:30.656
God, he's sick.

37:30.681 --> 37:33.288
He does not deserve
to spend his last days

37:33.313 --> 37:35.655
hounded by scandal and shame.

37:35.680 --> 37:38.733
Maybe he doesn't,
but if Karl's caught in the crossfire,

37:38.758 --> 37:41.844
it's only because he's been
standing too close to you.

37:43.514 --> 37:45.471
Naomi, I am begging.

37:45.905 --> 37:48.307
Blame me, destroy me.

37:48.332 --> 37:50.624
I promise I won't fight back.

37:50.649 --> 37:52.999
But please leave Karl out of it.

38:00.599 --> 38:01.655
Mom.

38:03.363 --> 38:05.092
What have you done?

38:15.566 --> 38:16.874
Eli.

38:18.021 --> 38:19.397
Are you his wife?

38:19.422 --> 38:20.436
Yeah.

38:22.049 --> 38:24.631
Is he okay? Why...
why is he unconscious?

38:24.656 --> 38:26.319
He needed to be sedated.

38:26.344 --> 38:28.819
His ribs are fractured,
but he'll recover.

38:28.844 --> 38:30.561
Oh, thank God.

38:30.586 --> 38:33.022
Before we put him out,
he was asking for you.

38:33.047 --> 38:34.913
We told him you were on your way.

38:34.938 --> 38:37.065
I came as fast as I could.

38:37.226 --> 38:38.811
He wrote you this note.

38:39.090 --> 38:40.850
Said it was important.

38:41.342 --> 38:45.569
_

38:47.567 --> 38:49.358
Everything okay?

38:51.390 --> 38:54.483
Yeah. I think it will be.

38:55.314 --> 38:58.452
It's gonna be a while
before he wakes up.

38:59.279 --> 39:01.365
Well, I'm gonna be here when he does.

39:19.536 --> 39:20.996
Mrs. Stanton.

39:21.459 --> 39:22.975
Hello, Claire.

39:23.280 --> 39:24.669
I need to speak to Rob.

39:24.694 --> 39:26.178
He's not here.

39:26.702 --> 39:28.569
How long until he returns?

39:28.815 --> 39:30.428
I'm not sure.

39:30.453 --> 39:32.011
Are you going on a trip?

39:33.053 --> 39:35.442
I'm going back home to Kansas.

39:35.467 --> 39:37.750
- For a visit?
- No.

39:38.217 --> 39:39.639
I'm leaving Rob.

39:40.061 --> 39:41.479
He's been having an affair.

39:41.504 --> 39:42.606
He doesn't know I know,

39:42.631 --> 39:44.315
and I thought I should
tell him in person.

39:44.340 --> 39:47.678
Oh, Mrs. Stanton, I'm so sorry.

39:47.951 --> 39:49.178
Thank you.

39:50.554 --> 39:52.733
Do you have any idea where he might be?

39:54.678 --> 39:56.389
He's at her apartment.

40:03.856 --> 40:05.944
So you've known about this.

40:07.113 --> 40:08.823
I wish you had told me.

40:08.848 --> 40:11.059
I thought we were friends.

40:11.944 --> 40:14.100
I haven't been your friend,

40:14.573 --> 40:16.452
not for one second.

40:16.914 --> 40:18.708
And you should hate me

40:19.233 --> 40:20.707
for everything I've done to you.

40:20.732 --> 40:22.359
What are you talking about?

40:23.861 --> 40:26.366
Rob's been cheating on you for years...

40:27.424 --> 40:29.553
with all sorts of women.

40:33.611 --> 40:35.334
And I was one of them.

40:39.811 --> 40:41.436
I was protecting you.

40:41.461 --> 40:42.702
By destroying their lives?

40:42.727 --> 40:43.850
She took advantage of you.

40:43.875 --> 40:45.793
No. I pursued her.

40:45.818 --> 40:47.177
And what we had, it was real.

40:47.202 --> 40:49.864
You only think that because
she twisted your mind.

40:49.889 --> 40:51.740
Trust me,
you are better off without her.

40:51.765 --> 40:53.592
No, maybe I'd be better off without you.

40:53.617 --> 40:54.716
Tommy...

40:54.741 --> 40:56.554
Dad always said that
you were vindictive,

40:56.579 --> 40:58.820
and I should get away from you
as soon as I got the chance.

40:58.844 --> 41:00.766
Your dad was a pathetic drunk.

41:00.791 --> 41:02.084
But he had your number.

41:02.109 --> 41:03.544
I'm leaving tonight.

41:03.569 --> 41:05.438
And I'll be on the first plane
to Europe in the morning.

41:05.462 --> 41:06.940
Well, you think I'm just
gonna pay for you to go

41:06.964 --> 41:08.036
traipsing around Europe?

41:08.061 --> 41:10.176
I'm 18. I have access to my trust fund.

41:10.201 --> 41:12.203
I don't need anything from you.

41:12.983 --> 41:15.249
I am still your mother.

41:15.733 --> 41:18.952
No, from now on, you're just
some lady that I used to know.

41:46.706 --> 41:48.139
[CAR ALARM CHIRPS]

42:00.851 --> 42:01.927
You pulling out?

42:01.952 --> 42:03.139
Not yet.

42:03.658 --> 42:05.491
I'm waiting for someone.

42:11.221 --> 42:12.874
You have to understand,

42:13.296 --> 42:15.341
I have wanted to tell you

42:15.366 --> 42:17.920
for years, but...

42:19.132 --> 42:21.928
Oh, God, I am so ashamed.

42:22.866 --> 42:24.999
I'm leaving him, Claire.

42:25.934 --> 42:27.853
It doesn't matter anymore.

42:28.233 --> 42:30.833
You won't feel that way
once I've told you the rest.

42:30.858 --> 42:32.827
There's something else?

42:34.551 --> 42:36.595
[SIGHS]

42:39.390 --> 42:42.092
The last time I slept
with your husband...

42:45.075 --> 42:46.868
... was the day your child died.

42:53.432 --> 42:55.714
CLAIRE: We were in your
bedroom at your old house...

42:55.739 --> 42:58.492
- [CAR DOOR SLAMS]
- ... when Rob heard a car door slam.

42:59.092 --> 43:00.786
He got up to see you and your daughter

43:00.811 --> 43:02.327
had come home early.

43:05.412 --> 43:07.608
He yelled at me to get dressed.

43:14.091 --> 43:16.510
You began dragging a trash can

43:16.535 --> 43:18.169
to the backyard,

43:18.194 --> 43:20.514
so we had time to run downstairs.

43:23.111 --> 43:25.321
I was going to hide in a closet,

43:25.545 --> 43:27.741
but Rob said it was too dangerous.

43:31.944 --> 43:34.036
So he told me to get out

43:34.061 --> 43:35.842
through the side of the house.

43:37.531 --> 43:40.100
So while you were coming
in the front door...

43:42.131 --> 43:43.804
Hey there.

43:43.829 --> 43:46.374
... I ran around
the side of the house...

43:49.611 --> 43:51.279
... and left through the gate.

43:52.280 --> 43:54.420
And I left it open.

43:57.963 --> 44:01.749
A few hours later,
someone from work called.

44:02.749 --> 44:04.905
They told me what had happened,

44:06.015 --> 44:08.717
and I instantly knew it was my fault.

44:18.162 --> 44:20.030
Oh, Mrs. Stanton,

44:20.819 --> 44:24.061
I can't even begin to
tell you how sorry I am.

44:29.564 --> 44:31.984
I have one question.

44:32.964 --> 44:34.632
What's that?

44:38.008 --> 44:41.584
Did Rob know you had
not closed the gate?

44:45.661 --> 44:48.327
I called him that night and I told him.

44:50.084 --> 44:52.420
And he said he could forgive me...

44:53.044 --> 44:56.163
if I never told anyone
else what had happened.

44:58.397 --> 44:59.952
And I didn't.

45:00.610 --> 45:02.608
I was so ashamed.

45:05.751 --> 45:07.128
[SOBBING]

45:07.153 --> 45:10.849
I know you can't forgive
me for what I've done,

45:10.874 --> 45:12.888
but I will spend the rest of my life

45:12.913 --> 45:15.709
trying to atone for what I did to you.

45:15.734 --> 45:18.695
[SOBBING]

45:19.545 --> 45:20.850
Get up.

45:30.102 --> 45:34.858
You did... a horrible thing, Claire.

45:38.861 --> 45:40.803
But I'll forgive you

45:43.061 --> 45:45.993
if you promise to do one thing for me.

45:46.018 --> 45:47.116
Oh...

45:48.107 --> 45:49.608
Anything.

45:56.978 --> 46:01.481
You will never tell another living soul

46:01.506 --> 46:04.131
that we had this conversation.

46:05.026 --> 46:06.087
What?

46:06.514 --> 46:08.599
Rob can't know.

46:11.676 --> 46:14.264
I've decided not to leave him.

46:15.837 --> 46:17.231
I don't understand.

46:17.256 --> 46:19.014
You don't have to.

46:20.069 --> 46:24.364
All you need to do is
give me your solemn vow.

46:24.763 --> 46:26.241
Do that...

46:27.077 --> 46:29.514
and you have my forgiveness.

46:31.138 --> 46:32.342
Okay.

46:34.355 --> 46:35.815
I promise.

46:39.788 --> 46:41.423
Thank you, Claire.

47:12.283 --> 47:13.367
Hey, girl,

47:13.392 --> 47:14.685
what are you doing here?

47:15.118 --> 47:16.483
She missed you.

47:16.508 --> 47:18.038
Jade.

47:19.008 --> 47:20.885
I hope you don't mind.

47:21.389 --> 47:24.217
I let myself in. Your lock's busted.

47:24.641 --> 47:27.288
Why do I get the feeling
that you busted it?

47:27.313 --> 47:29.381
Don't be mad. I wanted to see you.

47:29.406 --> 47:30.710
Why, so you could break my other leg?

47:30.734 --> 47:32.897
Oh, God, I'm so sorry about that.

47:32.922 --> 47:34.749
Things got a little crazy last time,

47:34.774 --> 47:37.186
but I'm trying to make it up to you.
[CHUCKLES]

47:39.067 --> 47:40.295
See you cleaned a little bit.

47:40.320 --> 47:41.991
It was kind of a pigsty.

47:42.257 --> 47:43.428
Not that I'm being critical.

47:43.453 --> 47:45.381
I know you've been busy with, um,

47:45.406 --> 47:47.319
jail and stuff.

47:47.726 --> 47:50.741
- And you're cooking?
- Yeah, pot roast.

47:51.031 --> 47:52.202
The recipe you like.

47:52.227 --> 47:54.092
Why aren't you cooking
for your rich friends

47:54.117 --> 47:55.834
in their fancy mansion?

47:56.215 --> 47:57.788
Did they kick you out?

47:57.813 --> 47:59.616
Eli found out about my past,

47:59.641 --> 48:02.519
so I packed up my stuff and I left.

48:03.952 --> 48:05.616
What a shame.

48:05.641 --> 48:06.725
[SIGHS]

48:06.750 --> 48:08.311
Did you talk to him?

48:09.002 --> 48:10.561
Now, why would you think that?

48:10.586 --> 48:12.964
Because you're the only
one who knows my real name.

48:13.390 --> 48:16.530
Hand to God, I did not tell Eli.

48:17.352 --> 48:19.146
Did you tell someone else?

48:19.811 --> 48:21.717
Taylor came to see me in jail.

48:22.291 --> 48:24.311
Oh, shit!

48:24.431 --> 48:26.319
Yeah, she offered to pay my bail

48:26.344 --> 48:28.388
if I ratted you out, so...

48:28.413 --> 48:30.249
Taylor is a lawyer!

48:30.274 --> 48:32.850
She knows people,
and the cops are still looking for me.

48:32.875 --> 48:34.256
I could end up in prison!

48:34.281 --> 48:36.381
Yeah, and I may be walking
with a cane for a year,

48:36.406 --> 48:37.952
so I guess we're even.

48:39.166 --> 48:41.842
I got to get out of town. I need money.

48:41.867 --> 48:43.851
- Don't look at me, I'm busted.
- Well, you must have something.

48:43.875 --> 48:45.476
Like, what about your
grandfather's watch?

48:45.500 --> 48:47.522
- What about it?
- Give it to me! I'll pawn it.

48:47.547 --> 48:48.924
The hell you will!

48:48.949 --> 48:52.209
Goddamn it, Duke! You owe it to me!

48:52.234 --> 48:54.538
You really fucked me this time!

48:54.563 --> 48:55.881
I don't owe you shit.

48:55.906 --> 48:58.076
Now get the fuck out of my house!

48:58.522 --> 49:00.600
You stay away from me.

49:00.625 --> 49:02.444
Again with the crazy eyes, huh?

49:03.939 --> 49:06.983
Look, baby,
just put the knife down, okay?

49:07.008 --> 49:08.358
Just put the knife...

49:11.766 --> 49:13.436
You're gonna pay for that.

49:13.585 --> 49:14.741
You think?

49:14.766 --> 49:17.522
